CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 3, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "For GIs Overseas - Gift Boxes - Members of the Young People's Department of the Pittsburgh Conference Branch, Women's Missionary Society, packing Red Cross Educational Boxes which will be sent to boys and girls in liberated countries. The gift boxes are small, but they held many school supplies.  Left to right: Clyde Jr., Yvonne, Joan and Linwood Woodson, Mrs. Elsie Meeks, supervisor; Jacqueline Richards, Thelma Denson and Rose Sanford. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women and children, from left: Clyde Woodson Jr., Yvonne Woodson, Joan Woodson, Linwood Woodson, Elsie Meeks, Jacqueline Richards, Thelma Denson, and Rose Sanford, packing Red Cross boxes of school supplies
